# CurrencyConverter

## Project Description

CurrencyConverter is a WPF application written in C#. It allows you to fetch the latest exchange rates from an external API and convert values between different currencies. The main technologies used in this project are: LINQ, HTTPClient, WPF, JSON parsing, and data model handling.

## Features

- Fetching exchange rates from an API ([openexchangerates.org](https://openexchangerates.org/))
- Converting amounts between selected currencies
- Simple WPF graphical user interface
- Error handling and input validation
- Parsing JSON data
- Currency rate data model

## Technologies

- C# (.NET)
- WPF
- HTTPClient
- Newtonsoft.Json
- LINQ (for data collection handling)

## Installation and Running

1. Clone the repository:
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/Nefil/CurrencyConverter.git
   ```
2. Open the project in Visual Studio.
3. Obtain an API key from openexchangerates.org and enter it in the code.
4. Build the project and run the application.

## Usage Example

Select currencies, enter an amount, click “Convert” – the application will fetch exchange rates from the internet and calculate the conversion.

## Potential Project Extensions

- Saving results to a database
- Conversion history
- Extended support for currencies and languages
- Additional LINQ operations
- Exporting data to files

